# AI Coding Assistant Guidelines & Workspace Rules

This file defines the specific preferences, rules, and workflows requested by the repository owner for any AI assistant working on this codebase.

## 1. Git & Commit Workflow
- **Commit Messages:** 
  - Always use **English**.
  - Always follow the **Semantic Commits** standard (e.g. `feat(ui): ...`, `fix(keyboard): ...`, `style(ui): ...`).
  - Keep messages **extremely simple, objective, and minimalist**. Avoid verbose explanations; be as direct and concise as possible.
- **Commit Control:**
  - **NEVER** run `git commit` automatically or after implementing changes.
  - Keep all code changes staged (`git add`) or unstaged in the local workspace.
  - Only execute a commit when the user explicitly requests it or inputs the conversational command `!commit` (e.g., `!commit` or `!commit "custom message"`).

## 2. Keyboard & Mapping UI Guidelines
- **Key Representation:**
  - All keyboard keys, button badges, and mapping tags in the visual layout and user interface MUST represent keyboard characters in **uppercase** (e.g., `A, W, S, D, SPACE, CTRL` instead of `a, w, s, d`).
